<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76767#p76767"><![CDATA[
Well, what I always do is to use consitional assembly (the .if, .else and .endif assembly directive) so that I can assemble either a NTSC or PAL ROM.<br /><br />However, if you get it to work with one it's easy to make it work on the other, it's just a removal of a few nops or stuff like that. I invite you to read <a href="http://www.romhacking.net/docs/419/" class="postlink">my raster timing doccument on RHDN</a> to know more about that stuff.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Fri Apr 15, 2011 8:24 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
