<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76751#p76751"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Status bar problem]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76751#p76751"><![CDATA[
Another thing to consider with this kind of timed code is the difference between PAL and NTSC. A PAL scanline is a few CPU cycles shorter than an NTSC one, so if you plan to have your game work on both kinds of consoles you'll have to detect the region on startup and store that information somewhere. Then, when waiting for an scanline to go by you'll need to check this variable and wait about 7 extra cycles if the console is NTSC.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=95">tokumaru</a> — Thu Apr 14, 2011 5:22 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
