<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76729#p76729"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Status bar problem]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76729#p76729"><![CDATA[
In fact you should probably avoid rewriting the palette unless there is really NO other way to get the status bar looking like you want to.<br /><br />If you must rewrite the palette, do it during HBlank time to avoid the colors showing problem, and rewrite only the colors the status bar will use (no need to rewrite the whole 4 BG palettes if the status bar only uses one of them for example).<br /><br />Writes to $2000 might not be required but won't hurt either.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=38">Bregalad</a> — Thu Apr 14, 2011 2:32 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
