<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76723#p76723</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76723#p76723"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Status bar problem]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7654&amp;p=76723#p76723"><![CDATA[
As you change the palette during render time, you can see the palette colors drawn on the screen.  To hide it, change the palette quickly during hblank time.  (pixels 256-341)<br />And you don't need the $2000 write to turn the ppu off.<br /><br />And you'll probably hit the OAM corruption bug when you try this on hardware.  Need to ensure that the turning off point is near the right side of the screen, but not past it, and it has to be on a scanline without sprites.  So use the bottom pixels of sprite #0, and delay for one scanline in order to avoid a scanline with sprites on it.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=53">Dwedit</a> — Thu Apr 14, 2011 1:36 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
